<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="365" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,546,1797]" pageId="7" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1735,1761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="365">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[883,1028,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="365">dolichanthus</emphasis>
, referring to the long spine-shaped cornuti.
</paragraph>
